ZH: 我的老伴儿是我的青梅竹马。
EN: My old partner is my childhood sweetheart.

ZH: 他和他的老伴儿一起过了五十年的幸福婚姻。
EN: He and his old partner have enjoyed fifty years of happy marriage together.

ZH: 老板被老伴儿气得火冒三丈。
EN: The boss was infuriated by his old partner.

ZH: 她的老伴儿去世后，她整个人都变得憔悴了。
EN: After her old partner passed away, she became completely haggard.

ZH: 我渴望能和我的老伴儿一起度过余生。
EN: I long to spend the rest of my days with my old partner.

ZH: 老伴儿之间的默契配合是一种默契。
EN: The tacit understanding between old partners is a kind of rapport.

ZH: 他们是一对老伴儿，再也无法分开。
EN: They are old companions who can never be separated.

ZH: 老伴儿之间必须相互尊重。
EN: Old partners must respect each other.

ZH: 老伴儿之间的沟通非常重要。
EN: Communication between old partners is crucial.

ZH: 我喜欢看老伴儿一起走在路上的样子。
EN: I enjoy watching old partners walking together on the road.

ZH: 他们是一对老伴儿，默契无需言语。
EN: They are old partners whose rapport needs no words.

ZH: 老伴儿之间有时候也会有争执。
EN: Old partners sometimes have disputes too.

ZH: 这对老伴儿相互依偎着，一起看夕阳西下。
EN: This pair of old partners snuggled up together, watching the sunset.

ZH: 虽然年事已高，但老伴儿仍然相互扶持。
EN: Despite their advanced age, old partners still support each other.

ZH: 老伴儿之间不仅要互相尊重，也要包容。
EN: Old partners should not only respect each other, but also be tolerant.

ZH: 老伴儿的默契是无法被替代的。
EN: The rapport between old partners is irreplaceable.

ZH: 他们是一对老伴儿，一起分享快乐和悲伤。
EN: They are old companions who share joy and sorrow together.

ZH: 我期待着能和我的老伴儿一起去旅行。
EN: I look forward to traveling with my old partner.

ZH: 老伴儿之间要相互支持，共同度过难关。
EN: Old partners should support each other and overcome difficulties together.

ZH: 老伴儿之间的默契常常让人羡慕。
EN: The rapport between old partners is often enviable.
